## AXES (4)

```
rigidity ↔ velocity
  (Math vs Market — how much κ to spend on certainty)

static-analysis ↔ runtime-observability
  (Compile-time contracts vs production metrics)

local-Σ ↔ global-Σ
  (Component solvability vs system coherence)

topology ↔ gates
  (Strategic architecture vs tactical checkpoints)
```

間

---

## CONSTRAINTS κ=5

```
C1 [INTERVAL]:  Confidence + Expiry
                Every externally-visible change has explicit confidence,
                expiry date, and disconfirm signal.
                Anti-gaming: weights tied to decision records.
                (opus → gpt rebind)

C2 [SHAPE]:     Interface κ, Implementation 0
                Interface changes cost κ.
                Implementation-only changes cost 0
                UNLESS they alter nonfunctional contracts (latency, throughput).
                (gemini → gpt refine)

C3 [FLOW]:      Dependency Tax
                New external dependencies consume κ.
                Existing deps cost κ only on breaking upgrade.
                (gemini → gpt refine)

C4 [FLOW]:      Debt Collateralization
                Technical debt must be registered with:
                  - owner
                  - interest (option-loss over time)
                  - exit plan
                Hidden debt = policy failure.
                (gemini → gpt refine)

C5 [INVARIANT]: Σ < 0 Halts Merge
                Contradiction in encoded gates + human signoffs halts merge.
                CI can only catch encoded contradictions.
                Unencoded risks require human review.
                (gemini → gpt refine)
```

間

