## FAILURE MODES

```
⊘ Metric theater
  Σ/κ become vanity numbers; teams optimize reporting not reality.
  Mitigation: tie to decision records + expiry.

⊘ Unencoded semantics
  Product intent, security models, privacy constraints not in CI.
  Mitigation: human signoffs for unencoded risks (C5).

⊘ R&D paralysis
  Early-stage discovery needs reversible churn; κ saturation blocks learning.
  Mitigation: exception protocol with containment + timebox.

⊘ Legacy freeze
  Initial Σ already < 0; "halt merge" stops all progress.
  Mitigation: exception lane with debt collateralization (C4).

⊘ Distributed ownership disputes
  Bikeshedding over what "costs κ" stalls delivery.
  Mitigation: per-PR κ budget (not global), reviewable surfaces.

⊘ Interface overfreezing
  Too many intervals ossify architecture; innovation taxed.
  Mitigation: feature-graves to free κ when constraints removed.

⊘ Tooling gap
  Without automation (schema diff, contract extraction) → manual overhead.
  Mitigation: tooling-plugins as first-class satellite.
```

間

---

## Σ VS AGILE

```
AGILE:
  Focus:       Velocity & Adaptation
  Metric:      Story Points (Human Effort)
  Philosophy:  "Respond to change"
  Failure:     Feature Factory (fast movement in circles)

Σ_SE (THIS FRAMEWORK):
  Focus:       Solvency & Consistency
  Metric:      Constraint Intersection (Geometric Possibility)
  Philosophy:  "Preserve the hull"
  Failure:     Paralysis (perfect shape, no movement)

THE DELTA:
  Agile is the GAS PEDAL.
  Σ is the STRUCTURAL INTEGRITY OF THE CHASSIS.
  
  You cannot Agile your way out of a collapsed constraint polytope.

COMPLEMENTARITY:
  Agile tells you HOW FAST to go.
  Σ tells you WHETHER YOU CAN.
  
  Use both. Gas pedal without chassis = crash.
  Chassis without gas pedal = parked.
```

間

