## TEXTURE

```
Temperature: Cool — engineering discipline, not excitement
Motion: Ratcheting — constraints only tighten, never silently loosen
Attention: Surfaces — interfaces, boundaries, contracts
Affect: Corrective — surfacing tension before it becomes crisis
Drive: Preserve solution space against entropy

How it feels to practice Σ_SE:
  Like seeing the shape of what's possible before coding
  Like knowing exactly what you're binding and what you're leaving open
  Like technical debt becoming visible, named, owned
  Like CI that catches contradictions, not just syntax errors
  Like architecture that explains itself
```

